ct(value),\n+                redactions,\n+            }\n+        }\n+        _ => RedactedValue {\n+            value: value.clone(),\n+            redactions: 0,\n+        },\n+    }\n+}\n+\n+fn redact_string(text: &str) -> (String, usize) {\n+    let bytes = text.as_bytes();\n+    let mut redacted = String::new();\n+    let mut redactions = 0;\n+    let mut last_written = 0;\n+    let mut index = 0;\n+\n+    while index < bytes.len() {\n+        if !is_candidate_byte(bytes[index]) {\n+            index += 1;\n+            continue;\n+        }\n+\n+        let start = index;\n+        while index < bytes.len() && is_candidate_byte(bytes[index]) {\n+            index += 1;\n+        }\n+\n+        if index - start < MIN_CANDIDATE_LEN {\n+            continue;\n+        }\n+\n+        let candidate = &text[start..index];\n+        if should_redact(candidate) {\n+            redacted.push_str(&text[last_written..start]);\n+            redacted.push_str(REDACTION);\n+            last_written = index;\n+            redactions += 1;\n+        }\n+    }\n+\n+    if redactions == 0 {\n+        return (text.to_owned(), 0);\n+    }\n+\n+    redacted.push_str(&text[last_written..]);\n+    (redacted, redactions)\n+}\n+\n+fn should_redact(candidate: &str) -> bool {\n+    !is_obvious_non_secret(candidate) && shannon_entropy(candidate) > ENTROPY_THRESHOLD\n+}\n+\n+fn is_candidate_byte(byte: u8) -> bool {\n+    matches!(\n+        byte,\n+        b'A'..=b'Z' | b'a'..=b'z' | b'0'..=b'9' | b'_' | b'-' | b'+' | b'/' | b'='\n+    )\n+}\n+\n+fn is_obvious_non_secret(candidate: &str) -> bool {\n+    is_uuid(candidate) || is_common_hash(candidate) || is_timestampish(candidate)\n+}\n+\n+fn is_common_hash(candidate: &str) -> bool {\n+    matches!(candidate.len(), 40 | 64) && candidate.bytes().all(|byte| byte.is_ascii_hexdigit())\n+}\n+\n+fn is_uuid(candidate: &str) -> bool {\n+    if candidate.len() != 36 {\n+        return false;\n+    }\n+    candidate.bytes().enumerate().all(|(index,